@node "intro" "Introduction "
@next "legal"
@prev "main"

@{i}Now That's What I Call A Pop Quiz @{ui}

Being, what I'd call an overly-interested person in music, at some point
in 1995, after experimenting with programming for the first time, I thought
about producing my own pop quiz.  Another 6 months down the line, and I
finished a game innovatively entitled, 'Pop Quiz of 1995.'  I never released
it because at the tender age of 15, and with little knowledge of
programming, I didn't believe the game was up to 'release' standard,
(whatever that standard is!).

However, I had always had this vision to release my own game on the Amiga.
If there was to be a game that I would release, it would have to be a pop
quiz of some sort.  Having tried and tested numerous pop quiz's, not one
could keep me entertained for longer than what I believed to be a bare
minimum.  So, like most Amiga programmer's, I set about writing my own
(releasable) pop quiz, to solve the problem.  The end result:

 @{b}NOW THAT'S WHAT I CALL A POP QUIZ @{ub}

which I believe to be better than any other pop quiz around (of course, I
may be biased, but certainly out of the ones I have played before, this is
definitely the best!).  Five fun rounds, followed by the all important, not
to be missed, most exciting climax ever! - the @{i}Top Ten@{ui} round.

@{i} Features @{ui}

  - 5 fun rounds with 3 variations and a Bonus round
  - a quick-fire final round
  - superb sound effects and music
  - 'quiz machine' type graphics
  - full version contains over 2400 questions#
  - 32 different pop music topics, covering easy listening, 50s, 60s and
    all types of music upto the present day
  - joystick friendly: can sit back and do everything using your joystick
    from the joystick port (apart from entering your name in the hi-scores)
  - a hi-score table is also included*

Make sure you read the section on @{"PLAYING THE GAME" link "playing" 0} before playing the
game for the first time, so as to understand the format and features of
Now That's What I Call A Pop Quiz.


